    {
      "name": "Introduction",
      "description": "Welcome to the 15Five API. Our API allows you to access the functionality of 15Five platform\nand integrate it into your own applications. The documentation is designed to help developers\nquickly and easily understand how to use our API to build innovative and powerful solutions.\nWhether you're a seasoned developer or just getting started, we're here to help you every step\nof the way. Feel free to reach out to us with any questions or suggestions, and we'll do our\nbest to assist you.\n\nThe 15Five API is organized around REST. Our API has predictable resource-oriented URLs,\naccepts form-encoded request bodies, returns JSON-encoded responses, and uses standard HTTP\nresponse codes and authentication.\n\n# Authentication\n\nThe 15Five API uses API keys to authenticate requests. You can create, view and manage your\nAPI keys in 15Five: **Settings -> Features -> Integrations -> Public API**.\n\nYour API keys carry many privileges, so be sure to keep them secure. Do not share your secret\nAPI keys in publicly accessible areas such as GitHub, client-side code, etc.\n\nAuthentication to the API is performed via HTTP Basic Auth. Provide your API key as the basic\nauth username value. You do not need to provide a password.\n\n    curl -H \"Authorization: $MY_15FIVE_API_KEY\" https://api.15five.com/api/public/hello\n\nAll API requests must be made over HTTPS. Calls made over plain HTTP will fail with 301\nredirect responses. API requests without authentication will fail.\n\n# Pagination\n\nMany top-level API resources have support for bulk fetches via \"list\" API methods.\nFor instance, you can list users, groups, people attributes, etc. These list API methods\nshare a common structure and in response include the following data:\n`count`, `next`, `previous`, and `results`.\n\nThe 15Five API also supports bulk user updates for easier and more efficient employee record\nupdates.\n\n# Rate limiting\n\nRequests to the 15Five API are limited to 5 per second. If you exceed this threshold your\nsubsequent API calls will be dropped. Exceeding the threshold doesn't result in your API\nkey suspension.\n\n# Versioning\n\nWhen backwards-incompatible changes are made to the API, a new, dated version is released.\nRead our API upgrades guide to learn more about backwards compatibility. For all API updates,\nview our API changelog below.\n\n# Changelog\n\n### October 2025\n- Updated **List objectives** endpoint (`/objective/`)\n  - Added `weight` field to the response\n\n- Updated **Create objectives** endpoint (`/objective/`)\n  - Added `weight` field to the request body and response\n  - Added `weight` field to key_results in the request body and response\n  - **Deprecated** `is_progress_aligned` field in favor of `weight` field\n\n- Updated **Update objectives** endpoint (`/objective/`)\n  - Added `weight` field to the request body and response\n  - Added `weight` field to key_results in the response\n  - **Deprecated** `is_progress_aligned` field in favor of `weight` field\n\n- Updated **Get objective details** endpoint (`/objective/{id}/`)\n  - Added `weight` field to the response\n  - Added `weight` field to key_results in the response\n\n- Updated **Create key results** endpoint (`/key-result/`)\n  - Added `weight` field to the request body and response\n\n- Updated **Update key results** endpoint (`/key-result/`)\n  - Added `weight` field to the request body and response\n\n### April 2024\n- Updated **List users** (`/user/`) and **Get user details** endpoint (`/user/{id}/`)\n  - Added `mention_name` field to the response\n\n- Updated **List groups** (`/group/`) and **Get group details** endpoint (`/group/{id}/`)\n  - Added `mention_name` field to the response\n\n### December 2023\n\n- Updated **List review cycles** endpoint (`/review-cycle/`)\n  - Added `hierarchy_update_ts` to the response (currently in testing phase, available on request)\n  - Added `hierarchy_update_ts` as ordering field option\n  - Added query parameters `hierarchy_updated_after`, `hierarchy_updated_before`\n    to enable filtering by hierarchy last update timestamp\n\n- Updated **Retrieve cycle participants information** endpoint\n  (`review-cycle/{id}/participants/`)\n  - Added `hierarchy_update_ts` to the response (currently in testing phase, available on request)\n  - Added `hierarchy_update_ts` as ordering field option\n  - Added query parameters `hierarchy_updated_after`, `hierarchy_updated_before`\n    to enable filtering by hierarchy last update timestamp\n\n- Updated **Reviews list** endpoint (`/review-cycle/{cycle_id}/reviews/`)\n  - Added `hierarchy_update_ts` to the response (currently in testing phase, available on request)\n  - Added `hierarchy_update_ts` as ordering field option\n  - Added query parameters `hierarchy_updated_after`, `hierarchy_updated_before`\n    to enable filtering by hierarchy last update timestamp\n\n### October 2023\n\n- Updated **List users** endpoint (`/user`)\n  - Added query parameter `is_company_admin` to enable filtering by company admin.\n\n- Updated **Retrieve cycle questions and answers** endpoint\n  (`/review-cycle/{cycle_id}/results/answers/`)\n  - Added `status` and `completed_on` fields to items in the `answers` array.\n  - Added query parameters `created_after`, `created_before`, `updated_after`,\n    `updated_before` to enable filtering by creation and last update timestamp\n\n- Updated **Retrieve cycle participants information** endpoint\n  (`review-cycle/{id}/participants/`)\n  - Added query parameters `created_after`, `created_before`, `updated_after`,\n    `updated_before` to enable filtering by creation and last update timestamp\n  - Added query parameter `user_id` to enable filtering by selected user\n  - Added query parameter `group_id` to enable filtering by selected group\n  - Added query parameter `order_by` to enable ordering by selected fields\n\n### September 2023\n\n- Added **Get all objectives history** endpoint (`/objective/history/`)\n  - Lists all objectives history\n  - Added a new section in the navigation to group objective history endpoints\n\n- Updated **List users** (`/user`), **Get user details** and **Edit user** endpoints (`/user/{id}`)\n  - Added `global_id` fields to the user object response\n\n- Updated **Retrieve cycle questions and answers** endpoint\n  (`/review-cycle/{cycle_id}/results/answers/`)\n  - Added `review_types` field to the items in the `questions` array,\n    and `metrics_display` field to items in the `answers` array.\n\n- Added **Retrieve cycle participants information** endpoint\n  (`review-cycle/{id}/participants/`)\n  - Lists all cycle participants, along with the information about their manager and\n    additional managers, nominated peers, and all existing reviews.\n\n- Updated **List review cycles** endpoint (`/review-cycle/`)\n  - Added `does_manager_review` and `does_self_review` fields to the response in order\n    to be able to determine all review types enabled for a cycle.\n\n- Updated **Get review cycle details** endpoint (`/review-cycle/{id}/`)\n  - Added `does_manager_review` and `does_self_review` fields to the response in order\n    to be able to determine all review types enabled for a cycle.\n\n- Updated **Create key results** endpoint (`/key-result/`)\n  - Added `create_ts` and `update_ts` to the response\n\n- Updated **Update key results** endpoints (`/key-result/`)\n  - Added `create_ts` and `update_ts` to the response\n\n- Updated **List objectives** endpoint (`/objective/`)\n  - Added query parameters `created_after`, `created_before`, `updated_after`,\n    `updated_before` to enable filtering by creation and last update timestamp\n  - Added query parameter `order_by` to enable ordering by selected fields\n  - Added `create_ts` and `update_ts` to the response\n\n- Updated **Create objectives** endpoint (`/objective/`)\n  - Added `create_ts` and `update_ts` to the response\n\n- Updated **Update objectives** endpoint (`/objective/`)\n  - Added `create_ts` and `update_ts` to the response\n\n- Updated **Get objective details** endpoint (`/objective/{id}/`)\n  - Added `create_ts` and `update_ts` to the response\n\n- Updated **Get objective history** endpoint (`/objective/{objective_id}/history/`)\n  - Added query parameters `created_after`, `created_before`, `updated_after`,\n    `updated_before` to enable filtering by creation and last update timestamp\n  - Added query parameter `order_by` to enable ordering by selected fields\n  - Added `update_ts` to the response\n  - Added `objective_id` to the response\n\n### August 2023\n\n- Updated **List people attributes value** endpoint (`/attribute_value`)\n  - Added query parameters `created_after`, `created_before`, `updated_after`,\n    `updated_before` to enable filtering by creation and last update timestamp\n  - Added query parameter `order_by` to enable ordering by selected fields\n\n- Updated **List people attributes** endpoint (`/attribute`)\n  - Added query parameters `created_after`, `created_before`, `updated_after`,\n    `updated_before` to enable filtering by creation and last update timestamp\n  - Added query parameter `order_by` to enable ordering by selected fields\n\n- Updated **List high fives** endpoint (`/high-five`)\n  - Added query parameters `created_after`, `created_before`, `updated_after`,\n    `updated_before` to enable filtering by user creation and last update timestamp\n  - Added query parameter `order_by` to enable ordering by selected fields\n\n- Updated **List answers** endpoint (`/answer`)\n  - Added query parameters `created_after`, `created_before`, `updated_after`,\n    `updated_before` to enable filtering by user creation and last update timestamp\n  - Added query parameter `order_by` to enable ordering by selected fields\n\n- Updated **List questions** endpoint (`/question`)\n  - Added query parameters `created_after`, `created_before`, `updated_after`,\n    `updated_before` to enable filtering by user creation and last update timestamp\n  - Added query parameter `order_by` to enable ordering by selected fields\n\n- Updated **List check-ins** endpoint (`/report`)\n  - Added query parameters `created_after`, `created_before`, `submitted_after`,\n    `submitted_before` to enable filtering by user creation and last update timestamp\n  - Added query parameter `order_by` to enable ordering by selected fields\n\n- Updated **List pulse answers** endpoint (`/pulse`)\n  - Added query parameters `created_after`, `created_before`, `updated_after`,\n    `updated_before` to enable filtering by user creation and last update timestamp\n  - Added query parameter `order_by` to enable ordering by selected fields\n\n- Updated **List Priorities** endpoint (`/priority`)\n  - Added query parameters `created_after`, `created_before`, `updated_after`,\n    `updated_before` to enable filtering by user creation and last update timestamp\n  - Added query parameter `order_by` to enable ordering by selected fields\n\n- Updated **List security audit events** endpoint (`/security-audit`)\n  - Added query parameters `created_after`, `created_before` to enable filtering by user creation timestamp\n  - Added query parameter `order_by` to enable ordering by selected fields\n\n- Updated **List vacations** endpoint (`/vacations`)\n  - Added query parameters `created_after`, `created_before` to enable filtering by user creation timestamp\n  - Added query parameter `order_by` to enable ordering by selected fields\n\n- Updated **List security audit events** endpoint (`/security-audit`)\n  - Added query parameters `created_after`, `created_before` to enable filtering by user creation timestamp\n  - Added query parameter `order_by` to enable ordering by selected fields\n\n- Updated **Reviews cycle** endpoint (`/review-cycle`)\n  - Added query parameters `updated_on_start`, `updated_on_end`,\n    to enable filtering by last update timestamp\n  - Added query parameter `order_by` to enable ordering by selected fields\n  - Added query parameter `create_ts`, `update_ts` fields to cycle response\n\n- Updated **Reviews > answers > list** endpoint (`/review-cycle/{cycle_id}/results/answers`)\n  - Added query parameter `create_ts`, `update_ts` fields\n    to participant, authors, questions and answers response\n\n- Updated **Reviews > performance-measurements > list** endpoint (`/review-cycle/{cycle_id}/results/performance-measurements/`)\n  - Added query parameter `update_ts` field to measurement response\n  - Added query parameters `updated_on_start`, `updated_on_end`,\n    to enable filtering by last update timestamp\n  - Added query parameter `order_by` to enable ordering by selected fields\n\n- Updated **Reviews list** endpoint (`/review-cycle/{cycle_id}/reviews/`)\n  - Added query parameters `updated_on_start`, `updated_on_end`,\n    to enable filtering by last update timestamp\n  - Added query parameter `order_by` to enable ordering by selected fields\n  - Added query parameter `create_ts`, `update_ts` fields to cycle response\n\n### July 2023\n\n- Updated **List users** endpoint (`/user`)\n  - Added query parameters `created_after`, `created_before`, `updated_after`,\n    `updated_before` to enable filtering by user creation and last update timestamp\n  - Added query parameter `order_by` to enable ordering by selected fields\n\n- Updated **List users** (`/user`), **Get user details** and **Edit user** endpoints (`/user/{id}`)\n  - Added `create_ts` and `update_ts` fields to the user object response\n"
    },
